-- Areva, BNP Paribas, RTL Group: European Equity Market Preview for Dec. 21
-- B y   K s e n i a   G a l o u c h k o
-- 2011-12-20T22:20:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-20/areva-bnp-paribas-rtl-group-european-equity-market-preview-for-dec-21.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in  European  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The  Stoxx Europe 600 Index  rose 2 percent to 238.51. The
 Stoxx 50 Index  climbed 1.5 percent to 2,306.92. The  Euro Stoxx
50 Index (SX5E) , a benchmark measure for nations using the euro,
increased 2.7 percent to 2,262.39.  Areva SA  (AREVA FP): The French maker of nuclear reactors
had its long-term  credit rating  cut two levels by  Standard &
Poor’s , which cited expected weak credit metrics and free cash
flow for 2012 as demand slowed following March’s nuclear
accident in  Japan . The shares gained 1.7 percent to 18.27 euros.  BNP Paribas SA (BNP)  : The French lender’s personal
finance unit faces a lawsuit from an association called EDC, in
the name of 33 investors, over loans in Swiss francs linked to
real-estate investments. The shares increased 6 percent to 30.14
euros.  RTL Group SA (RTL)  :  Europe ’s biggest television company
said it has appointed Guillaume de Posch as chief operating
officer starting Jan. 1. He will be responsible for corporate
strategy and business development, the company said in an e-
mailed statement today. The shares rose 1.5 percent to 72.90
euros in Luxembourg.  To contact the reporters on this story:
